Learning Splunk and SIEMs (Security info and event management)

Splunk analyse large amount of data. Splunk is a SIEM tool. 

Downloaded Splunk.

Started with event log collections collecting very basic data, 
selected logs are application, security and system. 

Searching events in the local system.

Searching with an asterisk* selects all the logs and shows them in a clear matter.

Creating a table to clearly see the information I am searching, query is 
* host="DANNY-PC" source="WinEventLog:Security" "EventCode=1102"
| fields - _bkt, _cd

|(pipe line) and fields - will remove columns that I do not want. 

Saving it onto dashboard.



